  "body": "\r\n```\r\npragma solidity ^0.8.0;\r\ncontract Fails {\r\n    function failWithNoReason(uint256 b) public view returns (uint256){\r\n        return 5 - b;\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\nconst Fails = await ethers.getContractFactory(\"Fails\");\r\nconst fails = await Fails.deploy();\r\nawait fails.deployed();\r\n\r\nconst result = await exploitable.failWithNoReason(7);\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe above fails with no reason because in v0.8.0 math operations cannot under/overflow. I don't know the underlying details, but it might be night to be able to detect this and say \"Transaction reverted because of underflow or overflow\" or something to that effect",
